The Grief of Being Honest

"Maybe I was stupid for not just lying on the application. Or maybe I wanted to test them with the truth."

🔥 Quote-worthy line

“My grief is not for what I lost. It’s for what I imagined you were.”

Writing seed: A piece titled “Honesty as a Filter, Not a Virtue”—how truth is your weapon and your test. Every gate that fails you reveals the cowardice inside the institution. Every rejection is proof they weren’t worthy.